# Atlas of Life - Project Context

## Project Overview
Atlas of Life is a life management application using cosmic metaphors. Current version: v0.2.16.2-chronos-concept

## Key Files
- `index.html` - Main page
- `js/app.js` - Core application logic
- `js/view_map.js` - Map rendering and Drag&Drop
- `js/state.js` - State management
- `styles.css` - Main styles

## Documentation
- `PRD_v0.3_Vision.md` - Product vision
- `CHRONOS_ENGINE_v0.3.md` - Time machine concept
- `IDEAS.md` - Ideas bank
- `CHANGELOG.md` - Change history

## Architecture
- JavaScript ES6+, HTML5, CSS3
- No external dependencies
- localStorage for data
- Canvas for map rendering
- Modular structure

## Key Concepts
- Domains = galaxies (life spheres)
- Projects = orbits (task groups)
- Tasks = stars (specific actions)
- Status flow: backlog → today → doing → done
- Priorities: p1 (critical) → p4 (low)

## Technical Preferences
- Microsoft Edge compatibility priority
- 60 FPS performance
- Viewport culling for optimization
- Pointer Events instead of Mouse Events
- Conventional Commits for Git

## Common Issues
- Edge bugs: limit requestAnimationFrame
- DnD bugs: check pointer capture
- Toast not showing: check z-index
- Performance: use throttling

## Constraints
- No external APIs, everything local
- No accounts, privacy is important
- No complex analytics
- No gamification
